Title: New Adventures Of Zorro

reviewText: Fantastic value on the "rare" 1981-82 Filmation Saturday morning series, shown originally in tandem with the Lone Ranger and Tarzan as the Lone Ranger/Tarzan/Zorro Adventure Hour. Even better is that you get ALL 13 remastered episodes (the complete series) for one low price. The episodes look fantastic, as they have been remastered, and the video is very clean with little to no artifacts. A MUST if you are a Zorro, Filmation fan, or just want to relive the best of Saturday mornings!
Title: New Adventures Of Zorro

reviewText: I remember on Saturdays and Sundays on I think CBS, they use to air this show. Back in the early 80s, Filmation did for the small screen what Walt Disney did for the movies. Filmation would go on to be famous for the first He-man series before it was surpassed by Ruby Spears and Sunbow. Great classic.

reviewText: Although made by the fine folks behind Masters of the Universe and Bravestarr the show has a different style of animation than it's better known Filmation siblings. As so, it has minimal stock footage and more fluid animation. The stories are pretty neat too!
